rows.item: All welds intact, not cracked or broken
No bent or broken tubing or sheet metal
All wheels secure and rolling properly
Front casters secure, rolling and swiveling properly (if equipped)
Wheel locks hold wheels securely when on and clear the wheels when off
No rips or cracks in seat or back rest
Restraint straps intact and working properly
Foot end carrying handles extend and lock properly
Head end carrying handles fold and unfold
Upper control handle extends and locks in all positions
Stair-Tread mechanism unfolds and locks properly
Stair-Tread belt inner cords not showing- replace if necessary
No lubricants present on the Stair-Tread belts or the track frame surfaces
Upper release handle cable not worn or frayed
Frame inspected for dents, gouges, & other signs of damage
Hoses inspected for rips, tears, & cracks
Straps & buckles inspected for damage and operate appropriately
Regulator inspected for dents, gouges, & other signs of damage
Heads-up display shows correct air supply level
Vibralert alarm activates when SCBA is turned on
Remote gauge inspected for dents, gouges, & other signs of damage
Remote gauge reads the same as the cylinder
Cylinder inspected for dents, gouges, & other signs of damage
Ensure latest hydrostatic test date is current
Cylinder pressure gauge is operable and reads 4500 psi
Cylinder valve hand wheel operates appropriately
PASS device activates when SCBA bottle is turned on
PASS alarm activates when pack is stationary
Mask inspected for rips, cracks, and other damage
Head harness inspected for rips, tears, & missing parts
Nose cup inspected for rips, tears, & cracks
